.TH "GENIGNORE" "1" "January 2026" "genignore" "User Commands"
.hy
.SH NAME
.PP
genignore - A utility for setting up .gitignores
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
\f[B]genignore\f[R] [template] [-h | \[en]help] [-a | \[en]append ]
[\[en]extend | -e] [-o | \[en]output ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
\f[B]genignore\f[R] generates \f[I].gitignore\f[R] files using
predefined templates corresponding to programming languages, build
systems, and environments.
.PP
If a \f[I]template\f[R] name is provided, the matching ignore rules are
generated.
.PP
Template names are case-sensitive and correspond to the internal
template identifiers shipped with the program.
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[V]-h\f[R], \f[V]--help\f[R] \[em] Show this help message and exit
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[V]-a\f[R], \f[V]--append <path to template>\f[R] \[em] Append the
specified template to the generated .gitignore
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[V]-e\f[R], \f[V]--extend\f[R] \[em] Extend the existing .gitignore
instead of overwriting it
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[V]-o\f[R], \f[V]--output <output path>\f[R] \[em] Specify an output
file for the generated .gitignore (defaults to \f[V].gitignore\f[R] in
the current directory)
.TP
\f[V]template\f[R]
The name of the template to generate (for example, \f[B]Go\f[R],
\f[B]Python\f[R], \f[B]Node\f[R], \f[B]Rust\f[R]).
.SH TEMPLATES
.PP
\f[B]genignore\f[R] ships with a large collection of templates covering
many programming languages, build systems, and environments.
.PP
The complete list of available template names can be found in the source
file \f[I]list.go\f[R].
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
Generate a Go \f[I].gitignore\f[R] file:
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
genignore Go
\f[R]
.fi
.PP
Generate a Python \f[I].gitignore\f[R] file:
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
genignore Python
\f[R]
.fi
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
\f[B]0\f[R]
Success.
.TP
\f[B]>0\f[R]
An error occurred (for example, an unknown template).
.SH SEE ALSO
.PP
\f[B]gitignore\f[R](5), \f[B]git\f[R](1)
